{{Infobox organization |name = Directorate General of Nursing and Midwifery |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1977 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.dns.gov.bd/ Directorate General of Nursing and Midwifery] |remarks = }}
'''Directorate General of Nursing and Midwifery''' is the central government body responsible for public nursing and midwifery in Bangladesh and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Lukewarm response to nurses' new uniforms|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/lukewarm-response-new-nurses-uniforms-1460365|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=27 September 2017|language=en|date=11 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Welcome to Directorate General of Nursing and Midwifery|url=http://www.dns.gov.bd/|website=dns.gov.bd|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref> Tandra Sikder is the present director general of the directorate.<ref>{{cite web|title=Welcome to Directorate General of Nursing and Midwifery|url=http://www.dns.gov.bd/Director.html|website=dns.gov.bd|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=A framework provides midwifery service a boost in Bangladesh -bdnews24.com|url=http://bdnews24.com/health/2017/06/22/a-framework-provides-midwifery-service-a-boost-in-bangladesh|website=bdnews24.com|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref>
==History== Directorate of Nursing Services was created in 1977 and was later changed to its current form. This was done to expand nursing training in Bangladesh and increase the number of nurses.<ref>{{cite web|title=Welcome to Directorate General of Nursing and Midwifery|url=http://www.dns.gov.bd/Background.html|website=dns.gov.bd|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref> The directorate falls under the jurisdiction of the [[Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (Bangladesh)]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Korea celebrates nursing day in Bangladesh|url=http://bdnews24.com/health/2017/05/15/korea-celebrates-nursing-day-in-bangladesh|website=bdnews24.com|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ICM developing midwifery accreditation guidelines as Bangladesh strengthening own policy|url=http://bdnews24.com/health/2017/06/20/icm-developing-midwifery-accreditation-guidelines-as-bangladesh-strengthening-own-policy|website=bdnews24.com|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref>
