'''Harvey S. Borovetz''' is an American bioengineer currently a Distinguished Professor and the  Robert L. Hardesty Professor at [[University of Pittsburgh]] and an Elected Fellow of the [[American Institute for Medical and Biological Engineering]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aimbe.org/coulter-foundation-awards-pitt-3-54-million-translational-bioengineering/|title=Awarded|publisher=aimbe.org|accessdate=November 9, 2018}}</ref> [[Biomedical Engineering Society]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bmes.org/content.asp?contentid=477|title=BMES List of Fellows|publisher=BMES|accessdate=November 9, 2018}}</ref> [[Council on Arteriosclerosis]], [[American Heart Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mirm.pitt.edu/our-people/faculty-staff-bios/harvey-s-borovetz-phd/|title=Harvey Borovetz|publisher=pitt.edu|accessdate=November 9, 2018}}</ref>

