[[Image:Restaurant Nora, Washington DC.jpg|thumb|right|200px|<center>Restaurant Nora</center>]] '''Restaurant Nora''' is America's first [[certified organic]] restaurant, located in [[Washington, D.C.]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thesalt/2015/05/12/404984547/in-organic-life-the-making-of-americas-first-organic-restaurant|title=In 'Organic Life,' The Making Of America's First Certified Organic Restaurant|last=Neary|first=Lynn|date=May 12, 2015|work=NPR|access-date=2017-07-20|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en}}</ref>
==Certification== To gain the certification, Chef Nora Pouillon proved that at least 95 percent of the [[ingredients]] used—including meats, vegetables, dairy, flour, coffee, chocolate, and oils—were from [[certified organic]] farmers and suppliers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.notablebiographies.com/newsmakers2/2005-La-Pr/Pouillon-Nora.html|title=Nora Pouillon Biography|last=|first=|date=|website=Encyclopedia of World Biography|publisher=Advameg, Inc.|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref> As a result, the restaurant's menu changes seasonally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.noras.com/nora/about/|title=About Restaurant Nora|last=|first=|date=|website=Restaurant Nora|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091216103335/http://www.noras.com/nora/about/|archive-date=December 16, 2009|dead-url=yes|access-date=}}</ref>
==Famous guests== In January 2010, President [[Barack Obama]] held a surprise birthday party for First Lady [[Michelle Obama]] at the restaurant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2010/01/michelle-obamas-surprise-birth.html|title=Michelle Obama's surprise birthday bash at Restaurant Nora|last=Akers|first=Mary Ann|date=January 17, 2010|website=The Washington Post|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/01/17/michelle-obamas-birthday_n_426199.html |title=Michelle Obama's Birthday Surprise Party At Restaurant Nora (PHOTOS) |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= 2010-01-17|accessdate=2013-12-05 |first=Alexander |last=Belenky}}</ref> Restaurant Nora has held lunches, dinners and events for dignitaries, congressional members and White House administrations, and was a favorite of [[Hillary Clinton]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thehill.com/capital-living/cover-stories/65541-the-home-of-organic-dining |title=The home of organic dining |publisher=TheHill |date= |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref>
